latestPosts.caption:
How my photography career started...

Quitting a comfortable 9-6 Design Engineer job for a passion was not an easy task at all. That too without any savings.😅 So in Feb 2020, I quit my job to start a new journey in photography.

Before Quitting the job, the major task was to convince & make it understand to my parents. It wasn't easy. Actually it took 1 year (i.e, from 2019) to make them understand about my view towards my passion😄

A month later entering into field, lockdown was announced, that is the major crisis I had. But it helped me alot actually because it changed the person who used to roam around & one who doesn't sit at a place to sit, think, learn, understand, tolerate so many things. Because of which I was built confident & focused towards my new career. It's been 2&half years and I am enjoying every bit of it. And a special thanks to @bhanuprathap.s & @50mm_studios for believing, understanding & supporting me all the time.

#photography #quitjob #passion #love #work #photographer #job #life

3 hard drives. All failed.
WD don’t offer data recovery.
Warranty? Yes. But trust? Lost.

I keep 2–3 backups because I’m a professional. But what about families or creators with just one drive?

@westerndigital @sandiskindia @sandiskstorage @sandiskstorage @teamsandisk @wdcreators @sandiskprohdd @sandisk — we need accountability.
